.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/Menu.png"}, {"caption": "Settings Menu", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/Menu1.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/Menu1.png"}, {"caption": "Handy Shortcuts", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/Menu2.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/Menu2.png"}, {"caption": "Settings Part 1", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/SettingsA.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/SettingsA.png"}, {"caption": "Power Dialog", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/Perform.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/handymenumate/screenshot/Perform.png"}], "short_description": "HandyMenuM8 lets you reboot or shutdown your PC with the least amount of clicks possible in Windows 8. I wrote it because I want to keep the Windows 8 Start Screen, without installing anything that would alter the way that the Taskbar / Start Screen works.\r\n\r\nHandyMenuM8 adds an icon to your System Tray, next to the time. When you right-click on its icon, it brings up a menu which will let you perform a Reboot / Shutdown / Hibernate / etc.\r\n\r\nIt also has a 'Handy Shortcuts' submenu, which will let you open some settings windows that is found within the Control Panel.\r\n\r\nThe latest version allows you to customize the icon, and allows you to edit the menu to show or hide only the options that you require.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\nWindows 7 (minimum) \r\nWindows 8 recommended\r\n.net Framework 4.0 (Already installed in Windows 8)\r\n", "shortname": "handymenumate", "socialnetworks": [{"accounturl": "", "socialnetwork": "Twitter"}, {"accounturl": "http://www.facebook.com/pages/Handymenum8/572253169468928", "socialnetwork": "Facebook"}], "status": "active", "summary": "HandyMenuM8 lets you reboot or shutdown you